OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMet Police apologises for  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F'openly Jewish' comment    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Met Police has apologised after an 
OL,6, officer said an antisemitism charity   
OL,7, leader looked "openly Jewish" as he was
OL,8, threatened with arrest for being near a
OL,9, pro-Palestine march.                   
OL,11,FGideon Falter was wearing a kippah     
OL,12,Fskull-cap when he was stopped in the   
OL,13,FAldwych area of London on Saturday.    
OL,15,FHe was told by police his presence was 
OL,16,Fcausing a "breach of peace", in a video
OL,17,Fposted online.                         
OL,19,FScotland Yard apologised for the       
OL,20,Fofficer's phrase.                      
